processHeading: Our Asphalt Paving Process
processIntro: >
  A long-lasting asphalt surface starts long before the first layer of asphalt
  is installed. Our process focuses on proper preparation, quality materials,
  and attention to detail to ensure your new driveway, parking lot, or private
  road performs for years to come.
processSteps:
  - title: "Site Evaluation & Planning:"
    description: >
      Every project begins with an on-site evaluation. We assess the existing
      surface, drainage, grading, and soil conditions to determine the best
      approach for your project.
  - title: "Excavation & Site Preparation:"
    description: >
      When necessary, we remove old pavement and unsuitable materials before
      preparing a stable foundation for the new asphalt.
  - title: "Base Installation & Compaction:"
    description: >
      A properly prepared aggregate base provides the strength and stability
      needed to support daily traffic while promoting proper drainage.
  - title: "Asphalt Installation:"
    description: >
      Hot mix asphalt is installed using professional paving equipment to
      create a smooth, consistent surface with the proper thickness for your
      project.
  - title: "Rolling & Finishing:"
    description: >
      Heavy rollers compact the asphalt while it's still hot, producing a
      dense, durable surface with clean edges and smooth transitions.
  - title: "Final Inspection:"
    description: >
      Before completing the project, we inspect the finished pavement to
      ensure it meets our quality standards and provide recommendations for
      curing and future maintenance.


